{"task":"transcribe","language":"english","duration":302.010009765625,"text":"The seasons of life, they turn like pages Some burn fast, some last for ages You love, you lose, you learn to pray You never think it'll break that way You hold on tight to what you miss Never knowing heaven's got a better script Than out of nowhere grace walks in A fire in her eyes and peace in her kiss Thank God for my last first kiss Struck like lightning, felt like this Heaven opened, time stood still All my broken roads led to her will My true love came, no doubt, no guess My life was waiting for that kiss If forever had a name, it'd be this Thank God for my last first kiss Some storms teach you who you are Some scars shine like guiding stars Every tear that once fell down Led me straight to my queen's crown The hurt is gone, the joy runs deep She's a promise my soul gets to keep When she smiles the whole world chills God knew exactly what I need Thank God for my last first kiss Struck like lightning, felt like this Safe and sturdy in her arms Wrapped in mercy, wrapped in calm A love so pure, no hit or miss I never knew love could feel like this My forever started with that kiss Thank God for my last first kiss I was searched, I was wandered Through nights I thought would never end But grace had written our beginning Before I knew where love had been Now I'm her king, she is my queen A fairy tale that's living Breathing what I needed, held and known In her arms I'm finally home Thank God for my last first kiss Struck like lightning, feel like this All the seasons led to her Every prayer was answered sure My destiny wrapped in bliss Have a signature in that kiss Forever starts and ends with this Thank God for my last first kiss Thank God If lightning strikes just once like this Let it always feel like this Yes, thank God for my last first kiss Yes, thank God for my last first kiss Yes, thank God, thank God, thank God, thank God For my last first kiss","words":[{"word":"The","start":13.